name: Memorial Park
directions: From the parking lot, follow the walkway that leads to 16th Street. The restrooms are along the walkway about halfway through the park.
comment: Six gendered, single-person restrooms. Two of them are pretty big, but I'm not sure if they're wheelchair-accessible. The big ones have changing tables, but I don't know if they're in working condition.

name: Douglas Park
directions: The restrooms are next to the tennis courts.
comment: Four gendered, single-person restrooms. Two of them have the icon of person in wheelchair next to the door. I don't remember if they have changing tables.

name: Penmar Park
directions: The restrooms are located on an outside wall of the building at the corner of Lake St and Glenavon Ave. The entrance to the parking lot closest to the restrooms is on Lake Ave, about 10 feet from Glenavon Ave.
comment: There's a changing table in one of them, but it was broken as of August 2023. I don't remember if they're wheelchair-accessible.

name: Whole Foods Market
directions: Back of store, by check-out line
comment: Requires a smartphone to scan and display a QR code for access, you may be able to get someone to hold the door for you

name: Waverly Park

name: Conejo Creek Dog Park
directions: Single restroom at west end of parking lot
comment: I don't remember if there's a changing table or if it's accessible

name: Playa Vista Sports Park

comment: Three unisex, single-person restrooms. There are changing tables in two of them. I don't remember if they're accessible.

name: Gong Cha

name: Airport Park

comment: Four gendered, single-person restrooms. Two of them have the icon of person in wheelchair next to the door, so they're wheelchair accessible.

name: Ike’s Love and Sandwiches
directions: Continue straight through, past all the visible tables, go into the small hallway in the back, both bathrooms are on the left. Separate gendered bathrooms but they’re single stall bathrooms, and both identical, plus it’s far enough away from people that nobody can see which bathroom you go into.
comment: Don’t have to be a paying customer. Separate gendered bathrooms but they’re single stall bathrooms, and both identical, plus it’s far enough away from people that nobody can see which bathroom you go into. Staff are transgender friendly.

name: JB Lovedrafts
directions: Immediately to the left after walking in
comment: This is a punk bar that is queer friendly, just walk with purpose, no one will bother, it's a popular spot for trans people.

name: Little Amps Coffee
directions: To the Left of the bar marked the Loo
comment: Baristas are nice, would suggest buying something, or browsing for a bit. It's a queer friendly space.

name: Circle K

name: Pamela & Edward Clark Hall
